Music Licensing, Inc. operates as a music performing rights organization. The company represents songwriters, composers, and music publishers. It issues music licenses for a monthly or annual fee, retains fee as revenue for Pro Music Rights, and collects the usage fees from businesses that use music, including television and radio stations; broadcast and cable networks; new media, including the Internet/streaming services and mobile technologies; satellite audio services; nightclubs, hotels, bars, restaurants, and other venues; digital jukeboxes; and live concerts. Music Licensing, Inc. was founded in 2018 and is based in Naples, Florida.